versions.description:
• Fixed a bug with the import of some sprites;
• Fixed import using Shapes2D asset;
• Fixed manuals.
Recommended for update.

Added:
• Automatic prefab creation for same components. Creating components from existing prefabs during next imports;
• Automatic downloading of missing fonts from the Google Fonts repository;
• Automatic coloring of single color sprites to white for color overlay using the Image component;
• Automatic project backup before each import and prefab creation;
• RectMask2D support;
• Import events (for customization, e.g., adding custom scripts to imported components, etc.);

Removed:
• Mipmap generation for downloaded sprites (for faster import);
• FCU_Button script (remains in the asset but is not used, will be replaced with an improved version in future releases);
• Relative positioning mode (with frame boundaries aligned to the boundaries of the Game tab) has been removed, and now Absolute positioning is used by default (frames are positioned as in the Figma layout);

Fixed:
• Algorithm for identifying identical objects;
• Many other fixes and improvements;

Fixed:
• Saving Figma session;
• TryAdd method on some versions of Unity;
• Downloading sprites on MacOS.

Fixed:
• Text positioning;
• Getting the download link for the sprite;
• Converting TextMeshPro fonts;
• Import using procedural image assets.

Added:
• RawImage support;

Fixed:
• Positioning of TrueShadow; 
• Enabling/Disabling of TrueShadow; 
• Identification of SDF font names; 
• Destroying of components during project reimport;

Known Issues:
• Bug with the display of the asset's interface in the settings tab when a TextMeshPro component is selected;
• Error in asset scripts when attempting to build (you need to delete the asset before building to fix this problem).

Added:
• Support for the 'Figma to UI Toolkit Converter' plugin has been added, providing the ability to import layouts from Figma into the UI Toolkit;
• Support for D.A. Button (formerly 'FCU Button');
• Support for positioning frames according to the borders of GameView.

Changes:
• Both manuals have been updated (information on importing sections has been added).
• Other fixes and improvements.

Changed:
• Improved positioning accuracy for objects with a rotation angle;
• Added Margin for TextMeshPro objects that have a ContentSizeFitter;
• Renamed 2 tags for Input Field, updated information in the 'Manual for designers'.

Fixed:
• Error when importing components using the Shapes2D asset;
• Error in the 'UNITY COMPONENTS' tab;
• Other fixes and improvements.

Added:
• Support for DTT's Procedural UI asset;
• Support for RTLTMPro asset;

Updated:
• Compatibility with Figma to UITK Converter;
Manuals.

Fixed:
• Other fixes and improvements.

Added:
• Support for DTT's Procedural UI asset;
• Support for RTLTMPro asset;

Updated:
• Compatibility with Figma to UITK Converter;
• Manuals.

Fixed:
• Fixed an error when importing a layout to UITK;
• Bug with namespaces;
• Other fixes and improvements.

Fixed:
• Exception when manually creating a prefab;
• Bug in the algorithm that determines which images need to be downloaded.

Fixed:
• Exception when creating prefabs: 'ArgumentNullException: Value cannot be null. Parameter name: path2';
• Bug where sprites with names starting with a dot were not being downloaded.

• Fixed NullReferenceException in CornerRounder.cs;
• Improved the algorithm for positioning objects with rotation;
• Improved caching algorithm;
• Other minor fixes and improvements.

Fixed:
• The issue where the USS file did not get populated with styles during re-import into UI Toolkit;
• NullReferenceException during import into UI Toolkit.

• Added support for "Nova UI";
• Fixed the font search algorithm;
• Added "Fonts" section in the "Manual for developers";
• Changed the positioning algorithm;
• Other fixes and improvements.

• Fixed incorrect positioning when using the "Layout Update" function;
• Added the option to import "Letter Spacing";
• Changed the caching algorithm for the recently loaded projects.

CHANGED:
• The import algorithm has been significantly rewritten: now, if you use procedural images, UITK, or Nova UI, the asset will attempt to draw your layout using the selected Unity component or framework, avoiding sprite downloads. If you use UIImage, your components will mostly be downloaded as sprites. This behavior of the asset can be configured.
In the "Manual for designers" you can find a link to the Figma project with import examples, as well as some frames you can import;
• You can adjust the import process using the "Download If Multiple Fills" and "Download Unsupported Gradients" functions, information about which you can find in the "Manual for developers";
• The "Destroy Childs" context menu function is now available for all GameObjects, not just the GameObject with the "FigmaConverterUnity" script. Do not use this function if you have not backed up your scene;
• The "FlexibleGridLayoutGroup" component has been replaced with "FlexLayoutGroup".

REMOVED:
• Unnecessary margins for text components when using TextMeshPro have been removed - now, if your text components appear incorrect upon import, you need to adjust it in the TextMeshPro font file;
• Unnecessary margins when importing to UITK.

ADDED:
• Support for the "FlexLayoutGroup" script from the "Unity UI Extensions" asset;
• A new "ignore" tag.

UPDATED:
• The "Manual for designers" and "Manual for developers".

FIXED:
• Error "RoundedImage could not be found" during asset import;
• Error "MainSettings does not contain a definition for UitkLinkingMode" during asset import;
• The function for automatic scene backups;
• Adding rectangular outlines to parent components.

CHANGED:
• To import images and emojis located at the root of the project, you need to place them in a Frame.

ADDED:
• The backup creation function has been added as a separate item in the context menu.

ADDED:
• Support for ScrollView drawing;
• Support for TMP_InputField drawing;
• Support for InputField drawing for password input.

CHANGED:
• InputField drawing;

FIXED:
• The algorithm preventing instantiation of components that should not be instantiated (e.g., invisible components);
• The 'ignore' tag.

ADDED:
• SVG support;
• Support for 9-Slice import from Figma.

FIXED:
• Exception when downloading a large number of frames due to Figma's 32-megapixel export limit;
• Several problems during layout import related to positioning of rotated elements;
• Exceptions in the 'Debug' tab after asset recompilation;
• Bug causing frames not to display in the asset UI before project import;
• Bug in the prefab creation algorithm that could lead to incorrect functioning;
• Bug in the Layout Update algorithm where components were incorrectly grouped under 'Components to Remove.'

REFACTORED:
• Localization creation algorithm;
• Object naming algorithm.

CHANGES IN INTERNAL LOGIC:
• Improved asset UI by dividing settings more accurately by category with several new settings added;
• Asset’s internal logic now uses Tasks instead of Editor Coroutines;
• Some asset scripts moved to a separate assembly.

DOCUMENTATION UPDATED:
• Updated developer manual with new asset UI descriptions and new features;
• Added information on Import Events functionality to the developer manual.

FIXED:
• Incorrect display of the frame list in the Inspector;
• NullReference and ArgumentReference exceptions during project import;
• 'Can only be called from the main thread' error;
• Reverted the fix for the error that caused frames not to display in the asset UI before project import.

• Fixed a bug that caused the build to fail;
• Optimized sprite downloading on the project's first import – identical sprites are no longer overwritten.

• Tagging algorithm is now faster, and tagging errors have been fixed.

FIXED:
• Errors occurring when the asset is installed before Json.NET is installed;
• Error in ScriptGenerator.cs related to TextMeshPro;
• Bug causing the asset interface to become transparent when switching between scenes.

FIXED:
• Bug where the last frame in the frame list was not displayed during import;
• Bug where the text inside some objects with the 'img' tag was not considered when determining uniqueness, causing them to overwrite each other during download.

• Fixed a bug where gradients were downloaded as white sprites;
• Full Rect and Pixels Per Unit are now set automatically; The improved 9-slice algorithm now creates rectangles with minimal size.
• Figma object info is now included in Import Events.

• Added support for importing the Selected state in the D.A. Button asset;
• Fixed compatibility with certain Unity versions;
• Assembly definition files moved outside the compiled assembly;
• Removed unused scripts.

• Added support for 'UITK Element Linker' asset;
• Version compatibility synchronization with Figma Converter for Unity;
• The script generator has been temporarily removed and will be added in version 1.0.6, as it needs to be updated for compatibility with 'UITK Element Linker' asset.

• Fixed a bug with namespaces;
• Fixed a bug with Parent.Id when importing a layout;
• Added support for 'UITK Element Linker' asset;
• Version compatibility synchronization with Figma Converter for Unity;
• The script generator has been temporarily removed and will be added in version 1.0.7, as it needs to be updated for compatibility with 'UITK Element Linker' asset.

• The UX for selecting the linking type has been changed. Now, instead of the two modes, Name and Guid, you can choose one of four states:
  1. Name - binding by unique name (works if the name is truly unique);
  2. IndexNames - binding by indexes and/or names of the element hierarchy;
  3. Guid - binding by unique GUID (the uniqueness of the GUID is guaranteed);
  4. Guids - binding by the hierarchy of GUIDs.

• The condition that the search for an element occurs by hierarchy if there are more than one element in the Names or Guids arrays is no longer relevant.
• Fixed an issue where an index of -1 was assigned when initializing elements of the Names array.
• Updated promo, minor changes in the context menu.
• Updated scene with examples.
